Indonesia Stocks: Agung Podomoro, Astra International, PT Inco

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-09-07T02:54:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/indonesia-stocks-agung-podomoro-astra-international-pt-inco.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:45 a.m. in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 30.17 points, or 0.8
percent, to 3,920.14, rising for a third day.  PT Agung Podomoro Land (APLN IJ), a property developer,
climbed 1.5 percent to 330 rupiah, set for the highest close
since Aug. 23. The company has acquired PT Putra Adhi Prima at a
cost of 300 billion rupiah ($35 million) and PT Karya Gemilang
Perkasa for 300.85 billion rupiah, Bisnis Indonesia reported,
citing Justini Omas, corporate secretary at Agung Podomoro. Omas
couldn’t be reached when called at her office.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ), Indonesia’s biggest
automotive retailer, advanced 1.1 percent to 69,250 rupiah. The
company’s unit, PT Astratel Nusantara, agreed to acquire a 95
percent stake in PT Marga Hanurata Intrinstic, which will
operate a 40.5 kilometer (25.2 mile) long toll-road in East
Java, Astra said. Astratel will pay PT Natpac Graha Arthamas 750
billion rupiah for the stake, Astra said.  PT International Nickel  Indonesia  (INCO IJ), or PT Inco as
the nation’s largest producer of the metal is known, gained 2
percent to 3,800 rupiah, rising for a fourth day. Nickel futures
climbed as much as 1.8 percent to $21,050 a metric ton in after-
hours trading in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
